r restructuring the right column to feature a \"Deterministic Simulation Viewer\" section based on agent selection. My goal is to ensure this simulation is prominently and gorgeously displayed, adhering to the requirements for a static frontend demonstration. The simulation will present \"user challenge,\" \"agent interpretation,\" etc, with clear CTAs.\n\n\n**Refining Display Logic**\n\nI'm now refining the display logic for the \"Deterministic Simulation Workflow Viewer\".  It needs to be *the* premium element, not buried. I'm focusing on the integration of key simulation elements: \"User Challenge,\" \"Agent Interpretation,\" \"Knowledge Needed,\" \"Actions Taken,\" \"Human Approval Point,\" \"Governance Check,\" and \"Expected Output Preview.\" The user will kick off the simulation with a button and then have these views.\n\n\n**Clarifying Simulation Details**\n\nI'm now integrating crucial details like \"Knowledge Needed,\" \"Actions It Would Take,\" \"Human Approval Point,\" \"Governance Check,\" and \"Expected Output Preview\" into the simulation. My focus is on ensuring these elements clearly define the workflow. I'm also preparing to add a prominent disclaimer to emphasize the static nature of the simulation. This is crucial for avoiding any misunderstanding about the frontend's static nature. I'm focusing on \"knowledge-needed\" datasets and step-by-step \"actions\".\n\n\n**Adding Call-To-Actions**\n\nI'm now focusing on integrating critical call-to-action (CTA) buttons within the deterministic simulation UI. I've confirmed the validity of the '/build/talk', '/build/blueprint', and '/build/foundry-studio' paths and will add them as custom related CTAs, either within the selected agent workspace or at the bottom of the workflow viewer, as a row of buttons. This should nicely fulfill the CTAs requirement. I'm also planning a prominent banner to clearly mark this as a safe, static simulation, and adding an interactive or animated workflow visualization.\n\n\n