nteractive visual components for the UI, starting with a disclaimer card at the top, a \"triggering challenge\" input box, an AI \"thoughts\" bubble for the `agentInterpretation`, a glowing knowledge vault, and a numbered action pipeline. I'm aiming for a modern, enterprise UI look and feel, incorporating a minimalist design with Apple-like elements.\n\n\n**Designing UI Enhancements**\n\nI'm now integrating CTAs (\"Talk to Agent,\" \"Blueprint Designer,\" and \"Foundry Studio\") into the `/build/sandbox` UI, specifically below the simulated output. I'm also finalizing the visual elements of the interactive components: a security badge for the human-in-the-loop checkpoint with an interactive approval slider, a \"sovereignty guardrail\" box highlighting GDPR compliance, and a formatted output box with a copy function. I'm exploring the current imports and type definitions.\n\n\n"}}
